      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ROCKY MONALOO (1) is a newcomer to the Seaton Grima stable from SA. Hasn't raced for 11 weeks but looks to be right up to the mark following a placing in a city trial and is likely to get the favours from the ace draw. HES MY REASON (9) made an immediate impact for the new yard when he led to cruise him by 11m at this circuit and distance. That made it three on the trot having won his previous two starts at Redcliffe. Draws on the back row this time but is going well. ROCKIN BULL (6) drew on the back row and was down the track over further last time but had kicked off the campaign with back-to-back seconds. Has a win and two placing in three tries at this shorter distance so worth another chance. THE CREEK (4) is worth some thought after his last-start fourth from this barrier.",
